subSubSection.paragraph:
Female genitalia: Very small (
Figs 77–81
); laterotergite (hemisternite) relatively small and wide, almost symmetrical, membranous apically, without setae and spines. Basal stylomere elongate, usually with few shot setae apically. Apical stylomere slightly shorter than basal stylomere, with short thick seta at ventral edge of outer margin, in ventral view curved, with comparatively narrow base (
Figs 78, 81
), in lateral view somewhat wide, parallel-sided or slightly narrowed apically, with rounded apex (
Figs 77, 79, 80
).
